cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new method for subspace clustering using a regularized linear model and provides experimental results to compare its performance with state-of-the-art methods. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Subspace clustering is a common technique in computer vision for grouping similar objects or features in images. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method and presents an active set algorithm for efficient optimization. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Subspace clustering can be used for community detection in social networks or for analyzing high-dimensional data in other types of networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses geometric analysis to study the properties of the elastic net regularizer and provides a theoretical justification for its performance.
